        "new_string": "def conditional_escape(text):\n    \"\"\"\n    Similar to escape(), except that it doesn't operate on pre-escaped strings.\n\n    This function relies on the __html__ convention used both by Django's\n    SafeData class and by third-party libraries like markupsafe.\n    \"\"\"\n    if isinstance(text, Promise):\n        text = str(text)\n    if hasattr(text, \"__html__\"):\n        return text.__html__()\n    else:\n        return escape(text)\n\n\ndef escape_with_encoding(text, encoding=\"utf-8\", strings_only=False, errors=\"strict\"):\n    \"\"\"\n    Convert text from a specified encoding to a Python string and HTML-escape it.\n\n    This function combines encoding conversion and HTML escaping in a single\n    atomic operation. It handles protected types (numeric/datetime objects) by\n    returning them as-is when strings_only=True.\n\n    Args:\n        text: The input to escape. Can be bytes, string, or other types.\n        encoding: The encoding name to use when decoding bytes (default: utf-8).\n        strings_only: If True, protected types (int, float, Decimal, datetime)\n                     are returned without conversion or escaping (default: False).\n        errors: The error handling mode for encoding errors like 'strict', 'ignore',\n               'replace' (default: 'strict').\n\n    Returns:\n        A SafeString containing the HTML-escaped result, or the original value\n        if it's a protected type and strings_only=True.\n    \"\"\"\n    from django.utils.encoding import force_str, is_protected_type\n\n    # Handle lazy translation objects by forcing to string\n    if isinstance(text, Promise):\n        text = str(text)\n\n    # If strings_only is True and the input is a protected type, return as-is\n    if strings_only and is_protected_type(text):\n        return text\n\n    # Convert to a Python string using the specified encoding\n    text_str = force_str(text, encoding=encoding, strings_only=strings_only, errors=errors)\n\n    # Apply conditional HTML escaping\n    return conditional_escape(text_str)\n\n\ndef format_html(format_string, *args, **kwargs):",
